    "description": "An embedded surface carries a Stable (or LTS) public claim only when its proof packet is within its freshness SLO, any waiver it relies on is unexpired, its evidence is complete, its claim manifest alignment is current, an owner has signed off, the surface carries owner/origin chrome, native-approval boundaries are host-owned, and browser fallback is available. A surface that loses any of those carries a label below the cutline (beta, preview, withdrawn) and never inherits an adjacent surface's published label."
